<h1>Boot Lacing</h1>
By Darxus@ChaosReigns.com, Mon Jul 19 22:58:21 EDT 1999
<p>This document attempts to depict some neat ways of lacing boots. Ladder
lacing (#1) is pretty common. #2 is something I came up w/ today. #3 is a
combination of #1 &amp; #2 I haven't tried, but I thought would be fun to
demonstrate combinations.</p>
<p>These layouts are specifically for boots w/ 8 pairs of holes. The patterns
can easily be extrapolated to whatever you want.</p>
<p>1st row is at the toe<br />
last row is at the top of the boot<br />
outside = what you actually see<br />
inside = what you'd see if you were in the boot</p>
<pre>
 
#1 ladder lacing:
 
outside  inside

  O--O   O  O
         |   \
  O--O   O  O|
           / /
  O--O   O |O
        /  \
  O--O  |O  O
        \ \
  O--O   O| O
          /  \
  O--O   O  O|
           / /
  O--O   O |O
         | \
 -O  O-  O  O
 

#2 what I like

outside  inside
  
  O  O   O--O
   \/    
   /\
  O  O   O  O
          \/
          /\
  O  O   O  O
   \/
   /\
  O  O   O  O
          \/
          /\
  O  O   O  O
   \/   
   /\
  O  O   O  O
          \/
          /\
 -O  O-  O  O
 
 
  O  O   O  O
 
 
#3 combination of #1 &amp; #2

outside  inside

  O--O    O  O
          |   \
          |   |
  O--O    O  O|
            / |
            | /
  O--O    O |O
          | |
          | \
  O  O    O  O
   \/   
   /\   
  O  O    O  O
           \/
           /\
  O  O    O  O
   \/   
   /\   
 -O  O-   O  O
       
       
  O  O    O  O

</pre>
<p>Yes, I was bored.</p>
<p>I'd show you how I tie my shoes too, but I think that'd be a bit much in
ascii :)</p>
